<TITLE> Joy arrives, at Hasina's house </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)Sajib Wazed Joy, son of prime minister Shiekh Hasina, and Dr M A Wazed Miah who died on Saturday, arrived in Dhaka on Monday morning from the United States. Joy drove straight to her mother's official residence Jamuna, Awami League deputy publicity secretary Ashim Kumar Ukil confirmed Joy's arrival. Communications minister Syed Abul Hossain had told bdnews24.com on Saturday that Joy had been trying to fly home as early as he could after the condition of Dr Miah breathed his last. Miah, 66, a nuclear physicist, died after prolonged illness in Dhaka on Saturday. He was buried at his family graveyard in his village home at Pirganj in Rangpur on Sunday. Joy had come to the capital in the first week of April to see his ailing father. He was among the entourage of the prime minister during her tour to Saudi Arabia. He returned to the US after performing Umrah. Daughter Saima Wazed Putul said she could not come because she and her newborn were sick, a family friend told bdnews24.com on Saturday. bdne
